events.name: Toronto Raptors at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Julius Randle had 31 points and 10 rebounds, RJ Barrett added 25 points and 12 boards, and the New York Knicks beat the Toronto Raptors 120-103 on Saturday for their ninth straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Knicks extend winning streak to 9, beat Raptors 120-103

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo scored 24 points and moved into second place on the Milwaukee Bucks’ career scoring list in a 132-94 romp over the Philadelphia 76ers on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Antetokounmpo has big day, Bucks trounce 76ers 132-94

headlines.description: — Malcolm Brogdon scored 26 points, Caris LeVert had 25 and the Indiana Pacers had a late 12-0 run to beat the Detroit Pistons 115-109 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pacers use late 12-0 run to beat Pistons 115-109

headlines.description: — Duncan Robinson made seven 3-pointers and scored 23 points, Kendrick Nunn had 22 and the Miami Heat held off a big Chicago rally to beat the Bulls 106-101 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Heat waste big lead, then hang on late to beat Bulls 106-101

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — DeMar DeRozan scored 11 of his team-high 32 points in the final 7:40 and made all 12 of his free throws in the San Antonio Spurs' 110-108 victory over the New Orleans Pelicans on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: DeMar DeRozan scores 32 points, Spurs beat Pelicans 110-108

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Dallas Mavericks

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic had 18 points and 13 assists and the Dallas Mavericks overcame a 17-point deficit to beat Los Angeles 108-91 on Saturday night in Lakers star Anthony Davis' second game back from a long injury absence.
headlines.shortLinkText: Doncic, Mavs beat Lakers 108-93 in Davis' 2nd game back

headlines.description: — Karl-Anthony Towns had 24 points and 12 rebounds to lead the Minnesota Timberwolves to a 101-96 victory over the Utah Jazz on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Timberwolves rally to beat Jazz in Utah for 2nd time

headlines.description: — Michael Porter Jr. scored a career-high 39 points, Nikola Jokic had 24 points and the Denver Nuggets beat the undermanned Houston Rockets 129-116 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Porter scores career-high 39 points, Nuggets beat Rockets
